USER

#1. At the beginning of the day the user gets notified to put offers
#2. The user is also notified of new data at each point in time
#3. The user analyzes the data received from the market and takes
    action on it.  An action is a list of orders or cancellations and
    new orders.

State of the user:
1. It has a money.
2. It has a portfolio of stocks.
2. It has a list of offers to made (it keeps track of the offers made to the market).
3. It has a list of companies to watch, based on the research done.
4. It looses money with each order carried.